Step 1: Launch EC2 Ubuntu Instance
Go to AWS Console
Launch an EC2 Instance
Choose:
AMI → Ubuntu Server 22.04
Instance type → t2.micro (Free tier)
Allow Inbound Rules:
SSH → Port 22
HTTP → Port 80
Launch and connect using:
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@your-ec2-public-ip
✅ Step 2: Install Docker on Ubuntu
Run these commands inside EC2:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
Start and enable Docker:
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
Check Docker version:
docker --version
(Optional: Run Docker without sudo)
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
newgrp docker
✅ Step 3: Create Project Folder
mkdir mywebsite
cd mywebsite
Create your index.html:
nano index.html
Example:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Docker Website</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello from EC2 + Docker 🚀</h1>
</body>
</html>
Save → CTRL+X → Y → Enter
✅ Step 4: Create Dockerfile
Inside same folder:
nano Dockerfile
Paste this:
FROM nginx:latest
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
Save and exit.
✅ Step 5: Build Docker Image
docker build -t my-nginx-site .
✅ Step 6: Run Docker Container
docker run -d -p 80:80 --name mycontainer my-nginx-site
Check running container:
docker ps
✅ Step 7: Open in Browser
Go to:
http://your-ec2-public-ip
🎉 You will see your index.html page live!

